            "bricType": "MultipleChoiceQuestion",
            "config": {
              "id": "QUE59002",
              "question": "Julian conducts an experiment at a formal retirement ceremony. When he is introduced to people at the ceremony, he shakes hands with his left hand as opposed to the usual right hand. What is the expected result of the experiment?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Everyone begins shaking hands with the left hand, and a new trend begins."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "People notice that Julian is different and admire his creative thinking."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "People become upset and confused, because a social rule has been broken."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "The women, who are trained to be more submissive, attempt to help Julian save face, while the men enjoy his embarrassment."
                }
              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "That’s correct!"
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Breaking social norms is often met with negative sanctions. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Norms are often strongly engrained within us and we tend to resist change. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Both men and women have been socialized to expect this norm of behavior. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                }
              }
            },
